{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Merged in PR #6","closed_at":"2026-03-24T06:08:34Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"f3b6529df883bdb3ad4bbffffbf2c4352de70e5e64b59c592c726840028888e2","created_at":"2026-03-24T03:07:24Z","created_by":"Jake Englund","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Every Harmony-OpenWRT device should automatically create/join an 802.11s mesh interface with SSID 'HARMONY-MESH' and PSK 'ZEBLITHIC'. This is intentionally well-known — Harmony provides E2E encryption (Reticulum + ML-KEM), so the WiFi layer is just transport. The mesh should auto-configure on install: add the mesh VIF to the 5GHz radio, set mesh_fwding=0 (Reticulum handles routing), set mcast_rate=24000. This replaces the current manual setup guide with zero-touch mesh peering. Any Harmony device within radio range automatically joins the mesh.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"harmony-openwrt-im5","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"zeblith@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Auto-join HARMONY-MESH communal WiFi network","updated_at":"2026-03-24T06:08:34Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"91525152b41199a468b66690e021005cc689c2c1701fa4384256b4519ced5dea","created_at":"2026-03-24T03:42:04Z","created_by":"Jake Englund","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"WiFi A-MSDU/A-MPDU aggregation doesn't work for broadcast frames (no BlockAck mechanism). The Harmony stack must perform its own batching: buffer outgoing Zenoh publishes and NDN announcements, concatenate into single 1024-byte payload blocks before transmission. Reduces total frame count and PHY preamble overhead.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"harmony-openwrt-lx0","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"zeblith@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":3,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"open","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Application-layer frame batching for broadcast efficiency","updated_at":"2026-03-24T03:42:04Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Merged in PR #7","closed_at":"2026-03-24T14:33:29Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"2b9c1f4a3c2ca6963c91b0d4544997baab28b0117c0e70823a97110314019ac2","created_at":"2026-03-24T03:07:24Z","created_by":"Jake Englund","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"On the HARMONY-MESH network, broadcast traffic is useful — CAS/NDN means overhearing content announcements, Bloom filters, and Zenoh scouting benefits all participants. Configure the mesh interface for broadcast-friendly operation: elevated mcast_rate, optimized beacon interval, tuned multicast-to-unicast settings. Investigate whether Zenoh's multicast scouting can leverage WiFi broadcast directly (UDP multicast → WiFi broadcast) without IP layer overhead. Research: can we use raw 802.11 data frames for Zenoh/Reticulum instead of IP, making the broadcast domain a native content-addressed network?","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"harmony-openwrt-ua3","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"zeblith@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Broadcast-optimized WiFi for CAS/NDN content sharing","updated_at":"2026-03-24T14:33:29Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Merged in PR #8","closed_at":"2026-03-24T15:12:08Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"331365b99f0ed4abeb5a59150774554b463df6adc66f835b1ec6866291be2e1a","created_at":"2026-03-24T03:42:03Z","created_by":"Jake Englund","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"802.11 power save causes DTIM buffering delays for broadcast/multicast frames. Harmony mesh nodes are always-on routers — power save is actively harmful. Add 'iw dev mesh0 set power_save off' to the init script or uci-defaults. Simple but important for broadcast latency.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"harmony-openwrt-yw6","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"zeblith@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Disable power save on mesh interface","updated_at":"2026-03-24T15:12:08Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"dbd37df4648bbcaf3897b74eeb591b7f557b7a7fa86e1cd9264daedf348c15cd","created_at":"2026-03-24T03:42:03Z","created_by":"Jake Englund","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Pad all raw Ethernet frames to uniform 1024-byte blocks before transmission to prevent traffic analysis based on frame size. An attacker on the public mesh can distinguish 500-byte Reticulum announces from 2KB CAS Bloom filters by size alone. Padding removes this signal. Negligible bandwidth impact with mcast_rate=24000. Requires raw Ethernet transport.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"harmony-openwrt-z3r","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"zeblith@gmail.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":4,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"open","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Fixed frame padding for metadata obfuscation","updated_at":"2026-03-24T03:42:03Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
